						<summary>

						<p>Pillar (No. 4) dug out from the main street in the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1074 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records the gift of one <hi rend="italic">mattar</hi> of land to the brāhmaṇa Śrīrayya by <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Sangamarasa who bears among others the epithet <hi rend="italic">lattalūrapuravarēśvara.</hi></p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 996, Ānanda, Uttarāyana Sankrānti. This may correspond to 1074 A.D., December 23, [Tuesday].</p>						

						</summary>
